  "live": [],
  "story": [
    "At the very summit, <b>Quince</b> is grinding out 6 clean sheets like a man morally opposed to fun &mdash; ugly, effective, and a touch boring. Hot on their heels, <b>Big Pewerk</b>'s lot have collectively decided defending is for cowards &mdash; 28 goals banged in (GD +1), spearheaded by Netherlands (beautiful football, then a fistfight among themselves). Rounding out the smug end of the table, <b>Sid</b> is the undisputed sultan of the stalemate: 5 draws and counting. Edge-of-the-seat stuff it is not.",
    "Wading into the midtable swamp, <b>Ike</b> is hauling Uzbekistan (the tournament's great unmarked mystery box) around like a dead fridge up a fire escape &mdash; it's played, and contributed the square root of sod all. Keeping them grim company, <b>Ellie</b>'s backline has the structural integrity of a wet paper bag &mdash; 28 shipped already, with Qatar (lavishly funded, modestly threatening) alone waving in 10. And clinging on by their fingernails, <b>Murray</b> bagged the pasting of the tournament so far, Japan (tidy, disciplined, devastatingly polite) romping home 4-0. Borderline rude.",
    "Down in the cheap seats, <b>Etan</b> watched Saudi Arabia (will park eleven buses and party at 0-0) get taken to the absolute cleaners 0-4 &mdash; a scoreline best discussed in hushed, pitying tones. And scraping the very bottom of the barrel, <b>Elsa</b> has spread the love like a sensible little pension fund &mdash; 4 teams all chipping in, not a single passenger. Boringly effective."
  ],
